{"title_page": "Edgar Britton", "text_new": "{{Short description|American painter}}\n[[Image:Mural- Petroleum Industry - Distribution & Use, by Edgar Britton at the Department of the Interior, Washington, D.C LCCN2013634345.tif|right|thumb|600px|Britton's mural ''Petroleum Industry: Distribution & Use'', on display at the [[Department of Interior]] in [[Washington, D.C.]]]]\n'''Edgar Britton'''  (1901 - 1982) was an American painter, muralist and sculptor born in [[Kearney, Nebraska]]. He moved to [[Chicago, Illinois|Chicago]]  where he studied and worked with [[Edgar Miller (artist)|Edgar Miller]].  There he began painting murals, many as [[Works Progress Administration|WPA]]  projects.<ref>Opitz, Glenn B, Editor, Mantle Fielding's Dictionary of American Painters, Sculptors & Engravers, Apollo Book, Poughkeepsie NY, 1986</ref>\n\nFor reasons of his health he relocated to Colorado in the early 1940s where he  taught at the [[Colorado Springs Fine Arts Center]] until 1951.<ref>http://www.chicagomodern.org/artists/edgar_britton</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Britton, Edgar}}\n[[Category:1901 births]]\n[[Category:1982 deaths]]\n[[Category:Modern painters]]\n[[Category:20th-century American painters]]\n[[Category:American male painters]]\n[[Category:American muralists]]\n[[Category:Artists from Colorado]]\n[[Category:Federal Art Project artists]]\n[[Category:People from Kearney, Nebraska]]\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|American painter}}\n[[Image:Mural- Petroleum Industry - Distribution &amp; Use, by Edgar Britton at the [[United States Department of the Interior|Department of the Interior]], Washington, D.C LCCN2013634345.tif|right|thumb|600px|Britton's mural ''Petroleum Industry: Distribution & Use'', on display at the [[Department of Interior]] in [[Washington, D.C.]]]]\n'''Edgar Britton'''  (1901 - 1982) was an American painter, muralist and sculptor born in [[Kearney, Nebraska]]. He moved to [[Chicago, Illinois|Chicago]]  where he studied and worked with [[Edgar Miller (artist)|Edgar Miller]].  There he began painting murals, many as [[Works Progress Administration|WPA]]  projects.<ref>Opitz, Glenn B, Editor, Mantle Fielding's Dictionary of American Painters, Sculptors & Engravers, Apollo Book, Poughkeepsie NY, 1986</ref>\n\nFor reasons of his health he relocated to Colorado in the early 1940s where he  taught at the [[Colorado Springs Fine Arts Center]] until 1951.<ref>http://www.chicagomodern.org/artists/edgar_britton</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Britton, Edgar}}\n[[Category:1901 births]]\n[[Category:1982 deaths]]\n[[Category:Modern painters]]\n[[Category:20th-century American painters]]\n[[Category:American male painters]]\n[[Category:American muralists]]\n[[Category:Artists from Colorado]]\n[[Category:Federal Art Project artists]]\n[[Category:People from Kearney, Nebraska]]\n", "name_user": "Mehendri Solon", "label": "safe", "comment": "fixed typo", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Edgar_Britton"}
